id7c6acdf0_ad1c_439f_ab10_679e6c1f0c}\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (b)\tab for the attendance 
of the youth at an educational or training course, a personal development program 
or a work program, project or camp; or\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (c)\tab for such 
compassionate purpose as the Chief Executive thinks fit; or\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (d)\tab for any purpose 
related to a criminal investigation; or\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (e)\tab for the purpose 
of enabling the youth to perform community service.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (2)\tab
{\field\fldedit {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK  \\l "id7c6acdf0_ad1c_439f_ab10_679e6c1f0c" }{\*\datafield }}{\fldrslt {Subsection (1)(a)
}}} does not apply if, in an emergency, it is necessary that a youth is removed 
from a training centre for a medical or psychiatric examination, assessment 
or treatment and the Chief Executive is advised as soon as practicable of the 
youth's absence from the training centre and the reason for the absence.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\keepn\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (3)\tab In determining 
whether to grant a youth leave of absence under this section, the Chief Executive 
must have regard to the following:\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (a)\tab the goals 
of the youth in respect of rehabilitation;\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (b)\tab the cultural 
needs and circumstances of the youth;\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (c)\tab the safety 
of the community;\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (d)\tab whether the 
youth has a history absconding or breaching orders;\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (e)\tab whether the 
youth is likely to interfere with a witness;\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (f)\tab the need 
that any victim of an offence committed, or alleged to have been committed, 
by the youth may have, or perceive, for physical protection from the youth.\par
{\*\bkmkstart id727c10f6_2dbe_4789_bd2e_d50749b982}\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\keepn\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (4)\tab Leave 
of absence under this section may be subject to 1 or more of the following conditions:{\*\bkmkend 
id727c10f6_2dbe_4789_bd2e_d50749b982}\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (a)\tab a condition 
that the youth will be in the custody of and supervised by 1\'a0or more officers 
or employees of the Department authorised by the Chief Executive for the purpose;\par
{\*\bkmkstart idf5c8e87b_c080_43d1_88ea_9c7829fd1d71_2}\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (b)\tab a condition 
that the youth be monitored by use of an electronic device;{\*\bkmkend idf5c8e87b_c080_43d1_88ea_9c78
29fd1d71_2}\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (c)\tab any other 
condition as the Chief Executive thinks fit.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (5)\tab A leave of absence 
under this section that allows a youth to leave the State may only be granted 
with the Minister's consent.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (6)\tab The Chief Executive 
may, by written order, revoke a leave of absence granted under this section, 
or vary or revoke any of the conditions to which it is subject.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (7)\tab A youth who 
is at large after the revocation or expiry of leave of absence may be apprehended 
without warrant by a police officer or an officer or employee of the Department 
authorised by the Chief Executive for the purpose.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (8)\tab A youth who 
is still at large after the expiry of leave of absence will be taken to be unlawfully 
at large.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (9)\tab A youth is not, 
while still at large after revocation of leave of absence, serving his or her 
sentence of detention.\par
