\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (b)\tab who is subject 
to a correctional order.\par
{\*\bkmkstart Elkera_Print_TOC61}{\*\bkmkstart Elkera_Print_BK61}\pard\plain\s177\f0\fs26\b\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb160\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\keepn\widctlpar\li567\ri0\fi-567 36\u8212 ?Transfer of young offenders 
to other States{\*\bkmkend Elkera_Print_TOC61}{\*\bkmkend Elkera_Print_BK61}\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (1)\tab The Minister 
may make arrangements with the appropriate authority of another State for the 
transfer of a young offender to that other State.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\keepn\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (2)\tab Before 
entering into arrangements under this section, the Minister must be satisfied\u8212 
?\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (a)\tab that any 
rights of appeal against the relevant correctional order have been exhausted 
or have expired; and\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (b)\tab that the 
young offender will be dealt with in the correctional system of the other State 
in substantially the same way as if he or she had remained in the correctional 
system of this State; and\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (c)\tab that the 
transfer is in the best interests of the young offender; and\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li1588\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1191\tx1588\tab (d)\tab that\u8212 
?\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li2382\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1985\tx2382\tab (i)\tab the young 
offender consents to the transfer; or\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li2382\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx1985\tx2382\tab (ii)\tab there are 
special reasons justifying the transfer although the young offender does not 
consent.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (3)\tab Before entering 
into arrangements under this section, the Minister must allow the guardians 
of the youth a reasonable opportunity to make representations on the question 
whether the transfer is in the best interests of the young offender.\par
\pard\plain\f0\fs23\expnd0\kerning0\cf0\sb120\sa0
\sl240\slmult1\ql\keep\widctlpar\li794\ri0\fi-794\tqc\tx397\tx794\tab (4)\tab Before consenting 
to a transfer, a young offender must be allowed a reasonable opportunity to 
obtain independent legal advice on the question of whether the transfer is in 
